    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54B32 3.2L inline-six power plant. This high-revving unit utilizes six individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory-spec variable M differential lock. Crucial preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a comprehensive subframe reinforcement, rod bearing replacement with VAC coated bearings, and a full VANOS bulletproofing. The suspension geometry remains precise with refreshed bushings and Bilstein dampers, ensuring the chassis handles with the hallmark communicative feedback expected of the M-division. While the finish shows minor road-rash consistent with its mileage, the mechanical synchronization and compression across all cylinders remain within tight tolerances.",
